22
00:03:02,296 --> 00:03:05,517
So, the sound design direction that we had for this game was...

23
00:03:06,813 --> 00:03:10,216
We wanted to try to get as far away from the game sounding

24
00:03:10,296 --> 00:03:13,718
gamey and let it sound more real, believable, immersive,

25
00:03:14,238 --> 00:03:16,299
and really put you in a galaxy far, far away.

26
00:03:18,220 --> 00:03:21,082
It was, of course, the most important thing

27
00:03:21,162 --> 00:03:22,983
to stay true to the Star Wars universe

28
00:03:23,303 --> 00:03:25,705
and make the game sound like the movies.

29
00:03:29,107 --> 00:03:32,909
We wanted to support the stories and create feelings

30
00:03:32,989 --> 00:03:35,971
and enhance the characteristics of the heroes and the villains.

31
00:03:38,413 --> 00:03:44,177
And it was very important for us that it sounded like the sounds were actually created in the world,

32
00:03:44,657 --> 00:03:49,541
interacting with the materials, the different environments and the characters,

33
00:03:50,201 --> 00:03:53,323
like the newer Star Wars movies, for example Rogue One.

34
00:03:54,144 --> 00:03:58,707
And this made the soundscape feel a bit more realistic and a bit grittier,

35
00:03:59,648 --> 00:04:04,931
although we at the same time strived to make a very clean and dynamic mix and readable for the player.

36
00:04:08,877 --> 00:04:10,257
Some challenges that we had,

37
00:04:11,097 --> 00:04:13,398
one of the big ones was mixed eras.

38
00:04:13,618 --> 00:04:17,560
We didn't only have the original trilogy,

39
00:04:17,580 --> 00:04:19,820
the prequel trilogy, and the sequel trilogy.

40
00:04:20,020 --> 00:04:21,961
We also had stuff from the cartoons,

41
00:04:22,501 --> 00:04:24,802
and you could say that we also created a new era

42
00:04:24,862 --> 00:04:27,663
with the single player story with Iden.

43
00:04:29,504 --> 00:04:31,964
And we wanted these to sound different from each other

44
00:04:32,225 --> 00:04:34,825
and make their individual contrasts stand out

45
00:04:35,106 --> 00:04:36,166
while still treating them

46
00:04:36,953 --> 00:04:39,334
with the same philosophy to make them fit

47
00:04:39,614 --> 00:04:40,774
into the shared soundscape.

48
00:04:44,195 --> 00:04:46,496
In order to handle all the abilities

49
00:04:46,576 --> 00:04:47,956
and the scope for this project,

50
00:04:48,336 --> 00:04:50,237
we needed to create smart solutions

51
00:04:50,597 --> 00:04:52,197
that would help us deliver fast,

52
00:04:52,277 --> 00:04:53,877
but still maintain high quality.

53
00:04:55,158 --> 00:04:57,158
So we created some versatile systems

54
00:04:57,198 --> 00:05:01,039
that could handle many different types of ability sounds.

55
00:05:02,059 --> 00:05:04,621
And these sounds, they shared strategies.

56
00:05:05,502 --> 00:05:09,545
And this system made it a lot easier to iterate.

57
00:05:09,925 --> 00:05:13,788
And you could do both general changes to all abilities,

58
00:05:13,868 --> 00:05:15,870
as well as individual tweaks per sound.

59
00:05:17,251 --> 00:05:19,332
And this really helped both the design process

60
00:05:19,993 --> 00:05:22,375
and maintaining the sound throughout the project

61
00:05:22,895 --> 00:05:23,816
and the mixing stage.

62
00:05:27,779 --> 00:05:30,921
We also wanted to focus a great deal on the gameplay feedback.

63
00:05:32,006 --> 00:05:37,150
We created a mix that was less compressed and clean and a lot

64
00:05:37,210 --> 00:05:40,112
more readable, with clear distance feedback

65
00:05:40,172 --> 00:05:43,455
and directionality and other important gameplay indications.

66
00:05:45,196 --> 00:05:47,858
So as I said, the mix was less compressed,

67
00:05:48,239 --> 00:05:50,560
and it left more space for each sound.

68
00:05:50,961 --> 00:05:52,842
And it was easier to give the power

69
00:05:52,882 --> 00:05:54,123
to a sound where it was needed.

70
00:05:55,592 --> 00:05:58,573
We also made distant content for all the abilities.

71
00:05:59,433 --> 00:06:02,374
And they are affected by the environment where they are

72
00:06:02,414 --> 00:06:04,535
created as well, where the sounds are created.

73
00:06:06,195 --> 00:06:11,017
And we also do a thing where the enemy sounds are higher in

74
00:06:11,057 --> 00:06:13,958
priority and louder than your friendliest sounds.

75
00:06:17,016 --> 00:06:21,038
We also really tried to focus on making different

76
00:06:21,199 --> 00:06:24,661
perspectives, so for example, when you are being affected

77
00:06:24,741 --> 00:06:27,983
by an ability, that was something that was important,

78
00:06:28,204 --> 00:06:31,446
and also dealing and taking damage so that you got

79
00:06:31,566 --> 00:06:32,306
feedback from that.

80
00:06:34,148 --> 00:06:36,810
We also in the sound design wanted to create clear

81
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:39,872
characteristics between the heroes and the villains

82
00:06:39,932 --> 00:06:43,394
as well as an individual character's own sound signature

83
00:06:43,695 --> 00:06:45,436
so that you could easily spot enemies.

84
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:50,571
One thing that is very hard when working with Star Wars

85
00:06:50,711 --> 00:06:54,733
is the lack of variation and also the gameplay abilities

86
00:06:54,813 --> 00:06:56,913
being different from the reference in the movies.

87
00:06:58,414 --> 00:07:01,936
And we always try to take the reference from the movies

88
00:07:02,016 --> 00:07:05,257
and try to expand, find elements, and recreate sounds

89
00:07:05,917 --> 00:07:08,618
and a variation in perspective, but still

90
00:07:08,758 --> 00:07:10,999
keep the character of the reference sound,

91
00:07:11,119 --> 00:07:13,220
but just making it fit gameplay, basically.

92
00:07:15,443 --> 00:07:18,766
Sometimes there was no reference or very vague reference in the films,

93
00:07:19,346 --> 00:07:23,389
but we needed to use the same recipes to make them fit into the Star Wars universe.

94
00:07:26,431 --> 00:07:29,154
Lucasfilm, they also wanted to approve some of our sounds,

95
00:07:29,754 --> 00:07:35,358
and something that was very important to them was that the Force sounds didn't sound too magical,

96
00:07:35,859 --> 00:07:38,701
too techy, or too similar to Marvel.

97
00:07:40,367 --> 00:07:46,794
And we tried to use the same principles as Ben Burtt, Matt Wood and David Accord to get the same feeling.

98
00:07:47,876 --> 00:07:53,823
And the direction from Lucasfilm was often less is more, or the more believable it was, the better they thought it was.

99
00:07:56,311 --> 00:07:58,852
In the game as well, sometimes the abilities

100
00:07:58,892 --> 00:08:00,593
have very little visual feedback.

101
00:08:00,953 --> 00:08:05,295
So a visual representation of an ability

102
00:08:05,335 --> 00:08:07,696
could just be an animation with a hand being lifted up

103
00:08:07,756 --> 00:08:10,817
in the air, like Darth Vader's force choke, for example.

104
00:08:11,337 --> 00:08:13,738
But the sound still needed to provide

105
00:08:13,758 --> 00:08:15,759
the diffuse but yet expected sound.

106
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:21,201
So let's move on to the examples.

107
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:23,882
And I will give three examples.

108
00:08:25,005 --> 00:08:28,986
I will start with Kylo Ren and his ability Force Freeze.

109
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:32,747
And for this example, I used almost exclusively

110
00:08:33,107 --> 00:08:34,668
the sound effects from the movie stems,

111
00:08:35,088 --> 00:08:36,348
and he's from the sequel trilogy.

112
00:08:37,789 --> 00:08:41,090
Next up is Darth Maul from the prequel trilogy

113
00:08:41,390 --> 00:08:44,791
and his ability Force Push, which had a clear reference,

114
00:08:44,911 --> 00:08:47,191
but I needed to make a hybrid with new sounds.

115
00:08:48,551 --> 00:08:52,993
And last but not least, Luke Skywalker and Force Repulse.

116
00:08:54,307 --> 00:08:56,048
And this had never been shown in any movie,

117
00:08:56,108 --> 00:08:58,169
so I had to come up with a completely new sound,

118
00:08:58,270 --> 00:09:01,052
but it still needed to sound original trilogy.

119
00:09:04,294 --> 00:09:06,536
I will show you a few scenes from The Force Awakens

120
00:09:07,396 --> 00:09:08,717
with Kylo Ren's Force Freeze.

121
00:09:12,846 --> 00:09:16,228
So yeah, Kylo Ren and his ability Force Freeze,

122
00:09:16,408 --> 00:09:18,549
which surprisingly freezes the opponent

123
00:09:18,609 --> 00:09:19,749
for a duration of time,

124
00:09:20,490 --> 00:09:21,830
which made this a looping ability,

125
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:23,171
it could differ in time.

126
00:09:24,212 --> 00:09:27,213
And as you saw, this ability had very clear reference

