00:09:29,934 --> 00:09:32,476
And I could base my sound almost entirely

129
00:09:32,636 --> 00:09:34,317
on the sounds from the movie stems

130
00:09:34,477 --> 00:09:37,018
and the sounds that Lucas or Skywalker Sound

131
00:09:37,098 --> 00:09:37,898
provided me with.

132
00:09:39,103 --> 00:09:41,785
Just a gentle massage to make them fit better into the game

133
00:09:42,045 --> 00:09:44,506
and some added elements for different perspectives

134
00:09:45,467 --> 00:09:46,728
and added variation.

135
00:09:48,469 --> 00:09:53,071
So when I started working on a new hero for this game,

136
00:09:53,271 --> 00:09:55,913
I always just wrote down a few words as a sound design

137
00:09:55,993 --> 00:09:58,274
direction for myself mainly.

138
00:09:58,754 --> 00:10:03,357
And for this character, I think Kylo Ren is, of course, evil.

139
00:10:03,577 --> 00:10:05,238
But he's still afraid as well.

140
00:10:05,881 --> 00:10:12,665
The sounds that David Accord made for him for the movie, they have a musical tone to them.

141
00:10:13,606 --> 00:10:20,711
They sound modern but also very distorted. So I started with extracting the sounds from the movie

142
00:10:20,731 --> 00:10:25,834
stems and I was quickly able to just make a loop out of the sounds.

143
00:10:27,102 --> 00:10:31,425
And I decided to split this looping sound into a noise

144
00:10:31,485 --> 00:10:32,766
layer and a tonal layer.

145
00:10:32,786 --> 00:10:35,307
And I will play you an example, and then I will tell

146
00:10:35,347 --> 00:10:36,128
you why I did this.

147
00:10:36,928 --> 00:10:39,550
So the first sound you will hear is the reference from the

148
00:10:39,570 --> 00:10:41,451
film and then my split loops.

149
00:11:13,811 --> 00:11:13,971
you

150
00:11:19,364 --> 00:11:22,025
So why did I do this?

151
00:11:23,126 --> 00:11:26,367
Since I split the loops, I could play them in two

152
00:11:26,387 --> 00:11:27,248
different samplers.

153
00:11:27,888 --> 00:11:29,809
And I could have set them in time from each other.

154
00:11:29,869 --> 00:11:33,190
I could also apply different randomization, like LFOs and

155
00:11:33,210 --> 00:11:36,712
the pitch and the amplitude, and just make a lot more

156
00:11:36,892 --> 00:11:39,133
randomization with quite short loops.

157
00:11:40,213 --> 00:11:43,715
And I could also route the tonal bass layer.

158
00:11:44,635 --> 00:11:46,597
into the subwoofer or the LFE channel

159
00:11:46,797 --> 00:11:51,782
without making the crisp noise layer unclear.

160
00:11:54,164 --> 00:11:56,786
After this, I needed to find some more variation

161
00:11:56,826 --> 00:11:58,407
for these sounds that I had extracted.

162
00:12:00,409 --> 00:12:02,991
But I of course wanted them to have the exact same feeling

163
00:12:03,011 --> 00:12:03,952
as the rest of the sounds.

164
00:12:04,933 --> 00:12:07,355
And especially for the affected perspective,

165
00:12:07,615 --> 00:12:09,177
I needed to add some sounds.

166
00:12:10,632 --> 00:12:18,393
So I started searching and I found this boomy Canon sound that had the same kind of tonality

167
00:12:18,473 --> 00:12:20,974
and very nice tone to it.

168
00:12:22,014 --> 00:12:24,795
And I also did some sound effects recordings myself.

169
00:12:24,915 --> 00:12:33,196
I bought this huge party balloon and I took my LS100 Olympus recorder, handy recorder

170
00:12:34,229 --> 00:12:39,034
And I just pushed the membranes straight into the balloon

171
00:12:39,114 --> 00:12:40,075
and then ripped it away.

172
00:12:40,095 --> 00:12:42,818
And this made a really nice ripping sound.

173
00:12:43,699 --> 00:12:46,261
And I just added some distortion on that, and then

174
00:12:46,301 --> 00:12:49,204
it sounded quite a lot like Kylo Ren.

175
00:12:49,865 --> 00:12:51,227
I will play those two examples as well.

